The weight of displays of new iPhones thus increased more than twice as much compared to previous generations.
In the case of a smaller iPhone from originally 12 grams to 29 grams, in the case of a larger one from 19 to 40 grams.
For iPhone 6s, the display is the hardest component used.
The weight of only 143 grams is then achieved with this news thanks to the fat loss that touched most of the remaining components.
For a larger model, the most difficult element used is the battery, but its weight has not changed compared to the predecessor.
