For their new studies, researchers from Min-Sheng General Hospital in Taiwan have used data collected from a study since 2007, which deals with two types of bariatric surgery - gastric bypass and gastriectomy - in treatment procedures for type 3 diabetes in people who were mildly obese.
The average BMI among those undergoing surgery dropped from 31 to 24,5 at the end of their fifth year, according to a study.
